715158f-c.title: Manhattan: 117th Street (East) - 3rd Avenue
715158f-c.text:
213 E. 117th Street, north side, east of Third Avenue,
showing a rear View of same and an empty 10t at the rearr as
viewed southward from 118th Street. The donors report reads-
''Reported to the Department of Buildings, December 10 1935;
visited January 8, 193o. The front was nicely boarded up but the
rear was open to a Vacant lot on E. 118th Street. There is a long
one story extension which formerly had sky-lights. Building appears
to be in a dangerous condition--pa t of the floor is gone, exposing
shallow sub-basement. The building and yard were swarming with
children.''
1936
Views: 1-2-3
0ift of Committee on Sousing
Charity Organization Society
CREDIT LINE ILPERATIVE
